NATIONAL LABOR RELATIONS BOARD v. MEAD’S BAKERY, INC. No. 7307. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. April 24, 1963. Dominick L. Manoli, Assoc. Gen. Counsel, and Marcel Mallet-Prevost, Asst. Gen. Counsel, N.L.R.B., Washington, D. C., for petitioner. Carl Bagwell, Oklahoma City, Okl., for respondent.

Before PICKETT and BREITEN-STEIN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Petition to enforce withdrawn, without prejudice, April 24, 1963, on motion of petitioner.
